  "response": "To cure dehydration:\n\n1. Drink plenty of fluids\n- Water\n- Clear broths\n- Electrolyte drinks (like Pedialyte)\n\n2. Oral rehydration steps\n- Sip small amounts frequently\n- Avoid large quantities at once\n- Drink slowly to help absorption\n\n3. Eat foods with high water content\n- Watermelon\n- Cucumbers\n- Soups\n- Fruits\n\n4. Avoid\n- Caffeine\n- Alcohol\n- Sugary drinks\n\n5. Rest and cool down\n\n6. Replace electrolytes with\n- Sports drinks\n- Electrolyte powders\n- Coconut water\n\nSeek medical attention if:\n- Severe symptoms persist\n- High fever\n- Extreme weakness\n- Inability to keep fluids down\n- Signs of severe dehydration (dark urine, dizziness)\n\nFor children and elderly, dehydration can be more serious, so monitor closely and consult healthcare professionals if symptoms are significant.",
